Elementary School Analysis - Charlotte, NC

Utilized "NC School Report Cards" as a Data Source (ncpublicschools.org)
Demographics pulled from schooldigger.com
Schools analyzed are within my geographical area of Charlotte
Updated 9-10-2019

"""
Kernal Density Estimation of all data. Skewed due to bias caused by loading specific schools
schools in the south charlotte area are much higher performing
Mean Performance = 76.14
Mean Achievement = 75.56
Mean Growth = 78.504
"""
f, axs = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(10,7))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
sns.distplot(datdf['Performance Score'], label = 'Performance')
sns.distplot(datdf['Achievement Score'], label = 'Achievement').set_title('KDE of All Schools Perf & Achiev Score')
plt.legend();

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
sns.distplot(datdf['Growth Score'], label = 'Growth').set_title('KDE of All Schools Growth Score')
plt.legend();

In [15]:
"""
Minor positive linear Correlation between Achievement and Growth Scores for all schools analyzed. 
"""
ax = sns.regplot(x="Achievement Score", y="Growth Score", data=datdf)
ax = plt.gca()
ax.set_title("Scatterplot - Correlation between Achievement and Growth")

print("R2 and P-value are:",scipy.stats.pearsonr(datdf['Achievement Score'], datdf['Growth Score']))

R2 and P-value are: (0.4131422884340402, 0.062675769028224)

Highly positive correlation between Achievement score and Performance Score.
